# Token Efficiency Rules

## Context Usage

- Do not load unrelated files.
- Do not paste long unchanged code.
- Use search first, then open only relevant files.
- Prefer exact file edits over broad rewrites.
- Keep summaries concise.
- Start a fresh task context when switching to a different feature.
- Use project memory files instead of long chat history.

## Agent Communication

- Handoff should be concise.
- Use file paths and bullet points.
- Do not copy large code blocks into handoff.
- Mention changed files instead of pasting full file content.
- Store important decisions in ADR files.

## Work Scope

- Bug fix should not become refactor.
- Refactor should not become new feature.
- New feature should not rewrite architecture.
- Documentation should not become novel writing. Please, society has suffered enough.
